This paper discusses the design and implementation of a Content Distribution Network (CDN) to improve Internet service quality. CDN involves replicating content from the place of origin to replica servers scattered over the Internet and serving requests from a replica server close to where the request originates. This topic is closely related to computer networks (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), system and control theory (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM).
